{ 4-Suit Jacoby Transfers - Transfer to Minors }

^-|cp||cs||at|^B@2^Y@3

This version of Transfer to Minors is very powerful but can be confusing because the traditional invitational 2NT bid by responder no longer is available. To make an invitational raise to 2N (since a direct 2N is a diamond transfer), you bid Stayman first and then 2N. Therefore, if responder bids Stayman, on rare occasions she will not have  a 4-card major. You should have a thorough discussion with your partner if you would like to use this version of transfer to minors.|
PG| ***** 112 ***** |


AT| 

One major benefit of this version is that the partnership  can use it to bid thin 3N games. For example, suppose your partner opens 1N and you have AQxxxx of diamonds. You might transfer to diamonds, and if partner bids 3C which shows 3 to the K, you bid 3N since you likely have 6 diamond tricks. Let me show you an example.|
